{"id":14881711,"mediaExerciseId":"87469558-9382-41d3-a62e-f2771e51fa99","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"20","chapterTitle":"Credit and Inventory Management","groupId":612458,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":699,"solutions":[{"id":6041615,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to explain what are sight draft, time draft, banker’s acceptance, promissory note and trade acceptance. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"a) Sight draft is a payment document by which the buyer undertakes to pay a certain amount immediately. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**  Time draft is a payment dokument by which the buyer confirms that he accepts the delivered goods and that he will pay the seller according to the pre-agreed conditions on the agreed date","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**  Banker’s acceptance is one of the types of payments where the bank guarantees that it will pay the commercial raft. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**d)**  Promissory note is a proof on paper prescribed by the bank which obliges the buyer to pay the debt to the seller. It is a means of securing payment, so if the buyer does not pay the amount he owes within the deadline, the seller has the right to cash the bill of exchange and thus collect his claim.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**e)**  Trade acceptance is a contractual obligation prepared by the seller for the buyer by which the buyer undertakes to pay for the goods purchased in the future. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"876bfd67-a857-453d-aa70-00edb876c466","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881712,"exerciseName":"2","page":700,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f53393aa-48f0-4887-9abd-bc6131656757","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-20-critical-thinking-questions-2-f53393aa-48f0-4887-9abd-bc6131656757"},{"id":14881713,"exerciseName":"3","page":700,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6bc5fa59-2b7e-461f-9e5e-72d3401ed3fc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-20-critical-thinking-questions-3-6bc5fa59-2b7e-461f-9e5e-72d3401ed3fc"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881710,"exerciseName":"8","page":697,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3b93a129-0889-4cc3-ab35-d846035c4449","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-20-critic